  "text": "Whole cell lysates were prepared as described previously. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Samples (20 g protein/lane) were separated by 12.5% SDS-PAGE, and Western blotting was performed using antibodies against mitogen-activated protein (MAP) kinases. [CITATION_3] Immunoblots were developed with horseradish peroxidase-conjugated secondary antibodies and a chemiluminescence kit (ECL Plus, Amersham Biosciences) and observed with LAS-3000 mini system (Fuji Photo Film, Tokyo, Japan).",
